==English==

===Etymology===
From the past practice of soldiers [[bite|biting]] a [[bullet]] to avoid crying out in pain, usually during a medical procedure or [[punishment]].

While this is given frequently as an etymology, [http://www.alt-usage-english.org/ucle/ucle10.html|1] suggests that this is in fact incorrect, and the phrase derives instead from the practice of biting open paper cartridges.

===Phrase===
'''[[bite]] [[the]] [[bullet]]'''

# To take a punishment or consequence with [[dignity]] or [[stoicism]].
# To accept a negative [[aspect]] in order to continue moving forward.

